Kenya Says 20 Companies Express Interest in Building Wind Farms

-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 
2011-10-04T10:29:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/kenya-says-20-companies-express-interest-in-building-wind-farms.html
Twenty companies have expressed an
interest in building wind farms in  Kenya , Energy Minister
Kiraitu Murungi said.  The East African nation’s Energy Ministry ordered Kenya
Electricity Generating Co., the nation’s monopoly power
producer, to identify a “suitable strategic partner” for wind
farms, Murungi said at a conference today in Nairobi.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah McGregor in Nairobi at 
 smcgregor5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  